CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 9, 1961, page A15 reads: "At JM Fete - Three members of the Junior Mothers chat happily with three members of the Pittsburgh Steelers' football team. The players were among those taking in the JM affair at the Horizon Room on Labor Day eve.  Left to right, are: John Henry Johnson, Mrs. Kay Jones, Gene (Big Daddy) Lipscombe [Lipscomb], Brady Keyes, Mrs. Frances Nunn and Mrs. Phyllis Pitts. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Pittsburgh Steelers football players John Henry Johnson, Gene "Big Daddy" Lipscomb and Brady Keyes, with Kay Jones, Frances Nunn, and Phyllis Pitts, standing in Horizon Room for Junior Mothers "Smart Affairs of 1961"
